    <note>Song(2) Wan [1583] His ancestors were a powerful lineage (dazu) of Guangping jun and later moved to Kaifeng, Xiangfu xian. Zhou Bida has the mingzi as Ying, but the career is the same as the man cited in the Song huiyao. Xiang's [8119] great grandson. Same generational name as Zhao [1559], Zheng [1560] and Bing [1573], and the other great grandsons of Xiang [8119] and Qi [1558]. His surviving son, Zhongfu [3795], has the same generational name as Zhongkan [1561]. Wan was buried in Hongzhou, Xinjian xian. Zhou Bida, WJ, 31.5a-13a. SHY:ZG, 69.22b. CBD, 1, 751.</note>
